Thanks Ken and Matt. This is really good information, especially learning
what rules of thumb you are operating by.

So, out of curiosity, if you do have the luxury of a larger population size
(presumably due to a problem with a quick fitness evaluation), where do you
recommend investing? More species, or larger species?

Is it better to have 100 species of size 30, or 10 species of size 300?

I am sure this too depends on the problem, but I would be interested in
hearing what people have found tends to work (or, at least, what they tend
to do). 




Cheers,
