&gt;&gt;&gt; I typically use around 150, but set the target species to 5 using a
&gt;&gt;&gt; changing compatability threshold.  This gives a rough specie size of
&gt;&gt;&gt; 30. I read somewhere, and I can&#39;t remember where, some article about
&gt;&gt;&gt; Highland cattle having to have a breeding population of 30 to make the
&gt;&gt;&gt; gene pool viable.
&gt;&gt;&gt; 
&gt;&gt;&gt; I guess its also a trade off with time also.  I am evolving Torcs
&gt;&gt;&gt; controllers for Julain Togelius&#39; CIG 2008 commpetition.  Each
&gt;&gt;&gt; controller takes around 4 seconds to evaluate.  If I had a pop of over
&gt;&gt;&gt; 1000, it would take a long time for my poor laptop to finish each
